{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"69e2d796-e2ba-45e3-a6e0-6ddf1a66c342","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump! A few things to note:\n\n1. **I don't have a specialized dump-analysis skill** — the `dump-collect` skill is only for *capturing* dumps, not analyzing them.\n2. **I'd need the dump file accessible in this environment** to help hands-on.\n\nHere's how you can analyze it depending on your platform:\n\n### Using `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump   # if not installed\ndotnet-dump analyze your-app.dmp\n```\nThen inside the REPL:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n- `pe` — print the last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n- `setthread <id>` + `clrstack` — inspect other threads\n\n### Using WinDbg (Windows)\nLoad the dump, then with SOS:\n```\n.loadby sos coreclr\n!pe           // print exception\n!clrstack     // managed stack\n!threads      // all threads\n```\n\n### Would you like me to analyze it here?\nIf you can share or upload the `.dmp` file to this environment, I can run `dotnet-dump analyze` interactively and help you find the root cause. Just let me know the file path!","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ec0feafa-262c-40f3-a77b-789e09dc7d05","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET app and wants to analyze it. Let me help them with this. I should look at what tools are available - I don't see a specific skill for analyzing .dmp files, but I do have the `dump-collect` skill. Let me check its description:\n\n\"Configure and collect crash dumps for modern .NET applications. USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps for CoreCLR or NativeAOT, capturing dumps from running .NET processes, setting up dump collection in Docker or Kubernetes, using dotnet-dump collect or createdump. DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze, profiling or tracing, or for .NET Framework processes.\"\n \nThat skill is specifically for collecting dumps, not analyzing them, so I'll need to guide the user directly on how to analyze their existing dump file using tools like dotnet-dump analyze, WinDbg, or lldb. I should ask where the dump file is located and what information they're trying to extract from it.","outputTokens":624,"requestId":"9423:2544DD:2B8B34:335BD3:69E82161"},"id":"d3edd12f-a18a-439e-8f2b-da2f6b4ef2fb","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:16:33.898Z","parentId":"4d70aceb-5696-45ad-b771-af794d60d9a5"}
